<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9421> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9421" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/10> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "ref. 418" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7634> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7634" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Monetalis. In MRR 2.434, and Index, 542, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.442-443, no. 418, 61 B.C. The moneyer was M. Pupius Piso, Pr. 44, son of the consul of 61. See below, on Pupius (12).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7254> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7254" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr. 44. Delete the gentilicium Calpurnius in MRR 2.319 and 434, and Index, 609. He was the son of RE no. 10, M. Pupius Piso M. f. Frugi, Cos. 61. Monetalis. In MRR 2.434, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.442-443, no. 418, 61 B.C. Quaestor, date unknown, but before 49 if he was Pompey's legate recruiting at Delos in 49 (see above, on no. 10, Cos. 61). Praetor 44. See MRR 2.319; Cic. Phil. 3.25; cf. Phil. 2.62, and Syme, CPh 50, 1955; JRS 50, 1960, 14-16-RP 2.501-503. ,\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5951> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5951" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He is named among those who were eligible for a praetorian province in the assignment made in the Senate meeting on November 28 (Cic. Phil. 3.25). See Sternkopf, Hermes 47 (1912) 386-388." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5597> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5597" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A Legate, who recruited troops for Pompey at Delos (Joseph. AJ 14.231)." .
